<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Crystal Palace captain Luka Milivojevic missed the vital sudden death penalty in an incredible shootout to allow Bournemouth through in the Carabao Cup second round.</p>

<p>The two sides couldn't be split in 90 minutes, and it took 21 penalties to find a winner in the shootout at the Vitality Stadium.</p>

<p>After all 20 outfield players scored, both goalkeepers missed - and then Milivojevic's second penalty was saved by Asmir Begovic.</p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

<p>Luka Milivojevic sees his penalty saved by Asmir Begovic to secure Bournemouth's victory</p>

<p>The scoreboard reads 11-10 on penalties following an incredible shootout at the Vitality</p>

<p>Sam Surridge fires the ball past Wayne Hennessey, only for his first-half strike to be ruled out</p>

<p>Ebere Eze (right) was making his first start for Crystal Palace in the Carabao Cup clash</p>

<p>Michy Batshuayi was also among a new-look forward line for the Eagles after returning on loan</p>

<p>Jack Stacey aims a shot towards Hennessey's goal but the Welsh goalkeeper is equal to it</p>

<p>Palace boss Roy Hodgson speaks to Bournemouth counterpart Jason Tindall on the touchline</p>

